<doc>
  <member name="ID3D10InputLayout">
    <summary>
      <para>An input-layout interface accesses the input data for the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-input-assembler-stage">input-assembler stage</a>.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This interface is created by calling <see cref="ID3D10Device.CreateInputLayout" />; use <see cref="ID3D10Device.IASetInputLayout" /> to bind it to the graphics pipeline.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-reference-d3d10-core-interfaces">Core Interfaces</seealso>
    <seealso cref="ID3D10DeviceChild" />
  </member>
</doc>